hands_on_practices.problem:
During early segmentation in the Drosophila embryo, pair-rule transcription factors (TFs) establish periodic spatial patterns that are integrated by the early enhancers of segment polarity genes to position the initial stripes of engrailed ($en$) and wingless ($wg$). Assume an idealized $8$-cell repeating array indexed anterior-to-posterior by $i \in \{1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8\}$, and the following presence ($1$) or absence ($0$) patterns of the pair-rule TFs across one repeat (values not listed are $0$). For each cell $i$, the set lists the TFs that are present:
- $i=1$: {Sloppy-paired (Slp)}
- $i=2$: {Slp, Runt}
- $i=3$: {Even-skipped (Eve), Runt}
- $i=4$: {Eve}
- $i=5$: {Slp}
- $i=6$: {Fushi tarazu (Ftz), Paired (Prd)}
- $i=7$: {Ftz, Odd-skipped (Odd)}
- $i=8$: {Odd}

Adopt the following simplified binding-site logic for the early enhancers, consistent with the idea that activators add and repressors subtract from a net regulatory input, and a fixed activation threshold determines transcriptional output. Let $\text{X}(i) \in \{0,1\}$ denote the presence of TF $\text{X}$ in cell $i$.

- For the engrailed enhancer, define the net input
$$S_{\text{en}}(i) \;=\; 1\cdot \text{Ftz}(i) \;+\; 1\cdot \text{Prd}(i) \;-\; 1\cdot \text{Eve}(i) \;-\; 1\cdot \text{Odd}(i) \;-\; 1\cdot \text{Slp}(i) \;-\; 1\cdot \text{Runt}(i),$$
and set the activation threshold to $\theta_{\text{en}}=2$. The engrailed gene is ON in cell $i$ if and only if $S_{\text{en}}(i) \ge \theta_{\text{en}}$.

- For the wingless enhancer, define the net input
$$S_{\text{wg}}(i) \;=\; 1\cdot \text{Slp}(i) \;-\; 1\cdot \text{Eve}(i) \;-\; 1\cdot \text{Ftz}(i) \;-\; 1\cdot \text{Odd}(i) \;-\; 1\cdot \text{Runt}(i),$$
and set the activation threshold to $\theta_{\text{wg}}=1$. The wingless gene is ON in cell $i$ if and only if $S_{\text{wg}}(i) \ge \theta_{\text{wg}}$.

Let $\mathcal{E} \subset \{1,\dots,8\}$ be the set of cell indices that activate engrailed and $\mathcal{W} \subset \{1,\dots,8\}$ be the set of cell indices that activate wingless under these rules. Compute the scalar quantity
$$Q \;=\; \sum_{i \in \mathcal{E}} i \;+\; 2 \sum_{j \in \mathcal{W}} j.$$
Report $Q$ as a single real number. No rounding is required.
